    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                        1779</dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Excuse me for Troubling you soon; but it is to beg that in case opportunity
                    offers by a private hand that you would send 4 of my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0028">Genera of birds</title></bibl> directed to me at
                        <persName ref="pe0146">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Longman’s</persName>
                    bookseller <placeName ref="pl2405">pater noster row</placeName>. the case is I
                    wish to have a few to send to foreign friends. The rest may go at leisure.</p>
                <p>If you have <persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Pope’s</persName> M.S. pray return it to him with my thanks. I lent it to
                        <persName ref="pe0058">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Cordiner</persName>
                    who has made some extracts from it with proper acknowledgements but it cost him
                    a deal of Labor.<note type="editorial">See Pennant's letter to Paton on <ref target="0247.xml">18 October 1778</ref> and notes.</note></p>
                <closer><salute>I am with best <lb/>wishes, Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> faithful humble Servt.</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennnant.</persName></signed></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p> I do not care how many of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0028">Genera</title></bibl> are sent hereafter by private hands by 2 or 3
                        in a parcel.</p>
                    <p>This moment y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> favour is come I shall desire
                            <persName ref="pe0146">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Longman</persName>
                        or somebody to call for the parcel at <persName ref="pe0043">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Cadels</persName>. the M.S. from <persName ref="pe0082">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> R<gap reason="illegible" unit="letters" quantity="1"/></persName> will be most welcome.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
